  <title><a href="/media-center/newsreleases/2022/national-study-finra-foundation-finds-us-adults-financial-capability" hreflang="en">National Study by FINRA Foundation Finds U.S. Adults’ Financial Capability  Has Generally Grown Despite Pandemic Disruption</a></title>
  <link>https://www.finra.org/media-center/newsreleases/2022/national-study-finra-foundation-finds-us-adults-financial-capability</link>
  <description>&lt;p&gt;WASHINGTON – On many measures of financial capability, U.S. adults generally fared better in 2021 than in the decade leading up to the pandemic, according to the FINRA Investor Education Foundation’s &lt;a href="https://www.finrafoundation.org/knowledge-we-gain-share/nfcs" target="_blank"&gt;nationwide, triennial study&lt;/a&gt;, published today. However, the research also shows that Americans’ financial wellbeing remains uneven across different demographic groups.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
