  <link>https://www.finra.org/media-center/newsreleases/2022/finra-orders-national-securities-corp-to-pay-9-million</link>
  <description>&lt;h2&gt;NSC Ordered to Pay Over $625,000 in Restitution to Customers Who Bought GPB Capital Private Placements After NSC Failed to Inform Them of Material Information&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;WASHINGTON—FINRA announced today that &lt;a href="https://www.finra.org/sites/default/files/2022-06/finra-letter-of-acceptance-waiver-and-consent-no-2019061652404.pdf"&gt;it has sanctioned&lt;/a&gt; National Securities Corporation (NSC) approximately $9 million, including disgorgement of $4.77 million in net profits the firm received for underwriting 10 public offerings in which NSC attempted to artificially influence the market for the offered securities.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
