  <title><a href="/media-center/newsreleases/2022/finra-appoints-michael-solomon-senior-vice-president-examinations" hreflang="en">FINRA Appoints Michael Solomon Senior Vice President of Examinations</a></title>
  <link>https://www.finra.org/media-center/newsreleases/2022/finra-appoints-michael-solomon-senior-vice-president-examinations</link>
  <description>&lt;p&gt;WASHINGTON—FINRA announced today that it has appointed Michael Solomon as Senior Vice President of Examinations. Solomon will assume this role on June 6 and report to Greg Ruppert, Executive Vice President and Head of Member Supervision.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solomon will be responsible for overseeing the strategic direction and execution of FINRA’s national Examination Program, assuming responsibilities previously held by Thomas Nelli, who retired from FINRA in March 2022.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
